[2] Turkey
Date: Wed, 18 Jan 2006
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: European Centre for Disease Prevention & Control (ECDC), accessed
18 Jan 2005 [edited] <http://www.ecdc.eu.int/>

Avian influenza in Turkey: situation update, 18 Jan 2006
--------------------------------------------------------
There are still confirmed H5 outbreaks in poultry in 13 different
provinces, and suspected outbreaks are [being] investigated in [a further]
19 of the 81 provinces of Turkey.
It should be [taken into consideration] that even one single bird with
confirmed H5N1 is counted as an outbreak.
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
[A map of confirmed and suspected poultry outbreaks in Turkey, updated 16
Jan 2006, is available at the ECDC website:
<http://www.ecdc.eu.int/images/maps/turkey_poultry_16jan06.BMP>.
According to the Turkish prime minister Recep Tayyip Erdogan on Tue, 17 Jan
2006, "Nearly one million poultry have been culled so far (due to bird flu)
in Turkey, and breeders were paid compensation,".
<http://www.turkishpress.com/news.asp?id=103777>. - Mod.AS]
